<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Calamagrostis</i> <i>muiriana</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Achillea</i> <i>millefolium</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>filifolia</i>, <i>Deschampsia</i> <i>cespitosa</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> spp., <i>Juncus</i> <i>drummondii</i>, <i>Juncus</i> <i>mertensianus</i>, <i>Oreostemma</i> <i>alpigenum</i>, <i>Penstemon</i> <i>heterodoxus</i>, <i>Potentilla</i> spp., <i>Ptilagrostis</i> <i>kingii</i> and <i>Trisetum</i> <i>spicatum</i>. Shrubs may be present at low cover, including <i>Kalmia</i> <i>microphylla</i>, <i>Phyllodoce</i> <i>breweri</i> or <i>Vaccinium</i> <i>cespitosum</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 0.5 m; cover is intermittent
to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Calamagrostis muiriana</i> > 25% nearest shoot frequency in the herbaceous layer (Ratliff 1982).</li>
		
		<li><i>Calamagrostis muiriana</i> > 30% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b); woody plants low in cover, including <i>Vaccinium cespitosum.</i></li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Subalpine to alpine seasonally flooded meadows, valley bottoms, flats, lower slopes.  </div>
</div>

        
