    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada</b> (M261Ek, En-o, Eq, Eu). Descriptions from Harvey Monroe Hall RNA (Taylor 1984, see Cheng 2004), Sequoia and Kings Canyon National Parks (Benedict 1983, Burke 1982, Ratliff 1982, Sumner 1941), Yosemite National Park (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b, Ratliff 1982, 1985), and generally (Potter 2005) characterize the alliance. The study in the Carson Pass area (Major and Taylor 1977) is near the northern range limit of <i>Calamagrostis muiriana.</i></li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> Many <i>Calamagrostis muiriana </i>meadows in the Sierra Nevada were summer sheep pastures in the 1800s and <i>Calamagrostis muiriana </i>Herbaceous Alliance 795 early 1900s (Potter 2005). Productivity of <i>C. muiriana </i>stands is likely intermediate between <i>Carex filifolia </i>stands on the low end and <i>C. nebrascensis </i>and <i>Deschampsia cespitosa </i>stands on the high end (Fites et al. 2007, Moore et al. 2000, Stohlgren et al. 1989). </div>
</div>

    

    

    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
